Here is a simple Java code to reverse an array:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        reverseArray(arr);
        for (int i : arr) {
            System.out.print(i + " ");
        }
    }

    public static void reverseArray(int[] arr) {
        int start = 0;
        int end = arr.length - 1;
        while (start < end) {
            int temp = arr[start];
            arr[start] = arr[end];
            arr[end] = temp;
            start++;
            end--;
        }
    }
}
```

This code uses a simple swapping technique to reverse the array. It starts from both ends of the array and swaps the elements until the middle of the array is reached.

